{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e357faf1-4688-4443-89dc-440e8e1ad334","content":"No repo-specific pipeline files found, so here's the general guidance:\n\n**Replace `VSTestTask@3` with `dotnet test`** using the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain `script` step). Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs as a regular `dotnet test` invocation.\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform** in your test project:\n```xml\n<!-- In your test .csproj -->\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Replace the pipeline task:**\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish TRX results:**\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n**4. Publish code coverage:**\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.coverage'\n```\n\n### Notes\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` uses the built-in Microsoft collector. For Cobertura format (cross-platform), use `coverlet` and `--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n- Add `condition: always()` to the publish steps so results are uploaded even on test failure.\n- If you run multiple test projects, add `--results-directory` to consolidate output in one place.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e51feb43-3fc8-4632-8e36-a991fb6950a1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have any relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":609,"requestId":"A03F:16E70A:BC3984:DCBD08:69FE85BC"},"id":"8e3fa05f-db2d-4cb7-8984-0dc21f4ce8c3","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:54:32.212Z","parentId":"9e11dc8f-6884-44cb-9af1-3ffae7107e25"}
